# Step 14: Update Bucket Policy

Go back to

Amazon S3

↓

Open Bucket

↓

Permissions

↓

Bucket Policy

↓

Edit

Replace the policy with the following template:

```json
{
  "Version":"2012-10-17",
  "Statement":[
    {
      "Sid":"AllowCloudFrontAccessOnly",
      "Effect":"Allow",
      "Principal":{
        "Service":"cloudfront.amazonaws.com"
      },
      "Action":"s3:GetObject",
      "Resource":"arn:aws:s3:::YOUR_BUCKET_NAME/*",
      "Condition":{
        "StringEquals":{
          "AWS:SourceArn":"arn:aws:cloudfront::YOUR_ACCOUNT_ID:distribution/YOUR_DISTRIBUTION_ID"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Replace

```
YOUR_BUCKET_NAME

YOUR_ACCOUNT_ID

YOUR_DISTRIBUTION_ID
```

with your actual values.

Click

**Save Changes**

---

## Explanation of Bucket Policy

**Version**

Policy language version.

**Effect**

Allows access.

**Principal**

CloudFront service.

**Action**

Allows reading objects.

**Resource**

Specifies all files inside your bucket.

**Condition**

Only your CloudFront distribution can access the bucket.

